Banks, Glorious Property, Ping An: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s   a n d   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-14T00:27:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/banks-glorious-property-ping-an-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in  Hong Kong  trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  gained 0.7 percent to 24,135.03. The
Hang Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H
shares of Chinese companies, increased 1 percent to 13,566.46.  Chinese lenders:  An increase in Chinese banks’ total bad
debt ratio to 30 percent is “not inconceivable” and that level
of non-performing loans would “likely be negative” for China’s
sovereign ratings, said  Andrew Colquhoun , the head of Fitch
Ratings’ Asia-Pacific sovereign debt unit.  Industrial & Commercial of China Ltd. (1398 HK), the
nation’s biggest lender, gained 1.2 percent to HK$6.59.  China
Construction Bank Corp. (939)  (939 HK), the second-largest, increased
1.2 percent to HK$7.46.  Bank of China Ltd. (3988)  (3988 HK) rose 1.2
percent to HK$4.41.  China Coal Energy Co. (1898 HK): The company said its March
coal sales volume climbed 17 percent from a year earlier. The
stock was unchanged at HK$10.58.  China Petroleum & Chemical Corp. (386)  (386 HK):  Asia ’s largest
refiner, known as Sinopec, plans to bid for exploration areas on
land and off the coast of northern  Brazil  later this year, said
Carlos Stenders, deputy general manager of Sinopec’s Brazil
operations. The stock rose 0.3 percent to HK$8.17.  Glorious Property Holdings Ltd. (845)  (845 HK): The developer
with projects in 10 Chinese cities said property sales in March
rose 229 percent to 1.1 billion yuan ($168 million) from a year
earlier. The stock lost 0.5 percent to HK$2.14.  Ping An Insurance (Group) Co. (2318 HK): China’s biggest
insurer said its unit Ping An of China Asset Management (Hong
Kong) Co. will launch the group’s first offshore yuan-
denominated bond fund. Ping An gained 0.8 percent to HK$84.90.  To contact the reporters on this story:
